### Button

You can create a button by adding the .btn class to any element. Once you create a button you can style it 
using a modular modifier approach. See examples below.

##### html
----------

```
<a href="#" class="btn">Default Link</a>
<button class="btn">Default Button</button>
<div class="btn">Default Div</div>
```

##### Let's style a button using modulr approach

##### html
----------

```
<a href="#" class="btn">Default</a>
<a href="#" class="btn purple">Purple Button</a>
<a href="#" class="btn border purple">Bordered Button</a>
<a href="#" class="btn border border-2 purple rounded">Bordered 2 - Rounded</a>
<a href="#" class="btn purple round">Purple Round</a>
<a href="#" class="btn purple round"><i class="fa fa-twitter"></i> Icon Round</a>
```

As you can see in example above, we use .rounded modifier class to add some rounded corners to our button. 
Default border-radius set in .rounded modifier is 3px, you can use .rounded-*size modifier to change 
the border-radius of rounded modifier. *size can be from 2 up to 20.

You can see in example above that we also have a icon in our button, if you want to create some space 
between icon en text, just add these classes to your .fa element. .prepend for when your icon is on 
the left side and .append for when your icon is on the right side. See a example below.

##### html
----------

```
<a href="#" class="btn green"><i class="fa fa-github fa-lg prepend"></i>Github</a>
<a href="#" class="btn blue">Google<i class="fa fa-google fa-lg append"></i></a>
```

> Since we're using Font Awesome icon library, you can change icons sizes by adding font awesome 
> icon size classes to .fa icon elements. For more info visit Font Awesome

##### Gradient & Glossy Button Modifiers

##### html
----------

```
<a href="#" class="btn blue gradient"><i class="fa fa-twitter"></i> Gradient Button </a>
<a href="#" class="btn pink glossy"><i class="fa fa-dribbble"></i> Glossy Button </a>
```

##### Let's see how we can change border width on .btn elements using .border-*width, 
##### *width can be from 2 up to 6. Default border-width is 1px;

##### html
----------

```
<button class="btn fill-red text-white hover-fill-green">
  Custom Button
</button>
<button class="btn border border-3 red hover-fill-green">
  Custom Button
</button>
<button 
  class="btn border border-3 purple text700 
  hover-fill-transparent hover-text-green hover-border-green">
  Custom Button
</button>
<button 
  class="btn l border border-3 pink margin-left 
  rounded-10 -rounded-top-left -rounded-bottom-right text700">
  Custom Button
</button>
```

##### Button Sizes

You can change the size of a button by adding one of the size classes to your .btn element. 
Default size is medium, other sizes are: .s for small .l for large, .xl for extra large and .xxl for extra extra large. 
See example below.

##### html
----------

```
<a href="#" class="btn s success">Small</a>
<a href="#" class="btn info">Medium</a>
<a href="#" class="btn l warning">Large</a>
<a href="#" class="btn xl danger">Extra Large</a>
<a href="#" class="btn xxl purple">Extra Extra Large</a>
```

##### Full Width Button: just add .width-100 class to any .btn element.

If you want your buttons to display a full width button when viewed on a mobile device, just add 
.mobile-full-width class modifier to your .btn element.

##### html
----------

```
<a href="#" class="btn l green width-100">Large Full Width Button</a>
```

### Icon Button

You can create icon buttons by adding an extra .icon class to your .btn element. See example below.

##### html
----------

```
<!-- Square Button  -->
<a href="#" class="btn icon blue"><i class="fa fa-twitter"></i></a>
<!-- Rounded Button  -->
<a href="#" class="btn icon blue rounded"><i class="fa fa-twitter"></i></a>
<!-- Rounded Gradient Button  -->
<a href="#" class="btn icon blue rounded gradient"><i class="fa fa-twitter"></i></a>
<!-- Rounded Glossy Button  -->
<a href="#" class="btn icon blue rounded glossy"><i class="fa fa-twitter"></i></a>
<!-- Round - Circle Button  -->
<a href="#" class="btn icon blue round"><i class="fa fa-twitter"></i></a>
<!-- Round - Border - Circle Button  -->
<a href="#" class="btn icon border blue round"><i class="fa fa-twitter"></i></a>
```

> You can also add .border-*width modifiers to your icon buttons as seen in button examples above.

