### Button Group

You can create a button group by wrapping your buttons inside a .buttons wrapper. See example below.

##### html
----------

```
<!-- Group Buttons Start -->
<div class="buttons">
  <a href="#" class="btn blue">Left</a>
  <a href="#" class="btn blue">Center</a>
  <a href="#" class="btn blue">Right</a>
</div>
<!-- Group Buttons End -->
<!-- Group Buttons Active Start -->
<div class="buttons">
  <a href="#" class="btn blue">Left</a>
  <a href="#" class="btn blue active">Center Active</a>
  <a href="#" class="btn blue">Right</a>
</div>
<!-- Group Buttons Active End -->
<!-- Group Buttons Round - Glossy - Active Start -->
<div class="buttons round overflow-hidden">
  <a href="#" class="btn glossy blue">Left</a>
  <a href="#" class="btn blue">Center</a>
  <a href="#" class="btn glossy blue">Right</a>
</div>
<!-- Group Buttons Round - Glossy - Active Start-->
```

##### Custom Button Group

You can create a custom button group by wrapping your buttons inside a .button-group wrapper and 
then you can use button and color modifiers to style your button-group. See example below.

##### html
----------

```
<!-- Remove border class makes it active + add hover-fill-disable to disable on:hover -->
<button class="btn border-2 blue hover-fill-disable">Left Active Button</button>

<!-- 
  add -border-v to center button, this will remove vertical (left & right)  borders 
  since left and right buttons already have active borders   
-->
<button class="btn border border-2 blue -border-v">Center Button</button>

<button class="btn border border-2 blue">Right Button</button>
```

##### Button Group Sizes

You can change the size of button groups by adding one of the size classes to your .buttons wrapper. 
Default size is medium, other sizes are: .s for small .l for large, .xl for extra large and .xxl for extra extra large. 
See example below.

##### html
----------

```
<!-- Small .s buttons start -->
<div class="buttons s">
  <a href="#" class="btn blue">Left</a>
  <a href="#" class="btn blue">Center</a>
  <a href="#" class="btn blue">Right</a>
</div>
<!-- Small .s buttons end -->
<!-- Medium .m or no extra size class: default buttons start -->
<div class="buttons m">
  <a href="#" class="btn blue">Left</a>
  <a href="#" class="btn blue">Center</a>
  <a href="#" class="btn blue">Right</a>
</div>
<!-- Medium .m or no extra size class: default buttons End -->
<!-- Large .l buttons start  -->
<div class="buttons l">
  <a href="#" class="btn blue">Left</a>
  <a href="#" class="btn blue">Center</a>
  <a href="#" class="btn blue">Right</a>
</div>
<!-- Large .l buttons end  -->
<!-- Extra Large .xl buttons start  -->
<div class="buttons xl">
  <a href="#" class="btn blue">Left</a>
  <a href="#" class="btn blue">Center</a>
  <a href="#" class="btn blue">Right</a>
</div>
<!-- Extra Large .xl buttons end  -->
<!-- Extra Extra Large .xxl buttons start  -->
<div class="buttons xxl">
  <a href="#" class="btn blue">Left</a>
  <a href="#" class="btn blue">Center</a>
  <a href="#" class="btn blue">Right</a>
</div>
<!-- Extra Extra Large .xxl buttons end  -->
```

### Button Addons

You can create button addons by wrapping your .btn element in a .btn-addon wrapper. 
Addons contain an extra .addon element. See example below.

##### html
----------

```
<!-- Example Twitter Start -->
<div class="btn-addon">
  <a href="#" class="btn m info"><i class="fa fa-twitter fa-lg prepend"></i> Follow</a>
  <a href="#" class="addon m info border">256</a>
</div>
<!-- Example Twitter End -->

<!-- Example Youtube Start -->
<div class="btn-addon">
  <a href="#" class="btn m red"><i class="fa fa-youtube-play fa-lg prepend"></i> Subscribe</a>
  <a href="#" class="addon m red border">3256</a>
</div>
<!-- Example Youtube End -->

<!-- Example Github Start -->
<div class="btn-addon">
  <a href="#" class="addon m brown border">128</a>
  <a href="#" class="btn m brown">Fork<i class="fa fa-github fa-lg append"></i></a>
</div>
<!-- Example Github End -->
```

##### Button Addons Border Size

When changing the .border-*width on your button addons, make sure that .addon as well as the .btn 
have the same .border-*width. See example below.

##### html
----------

```
<!-- Example Google Start -->
<div class="btn-addon">
  <a href="#" class="addon m blue border border-2 text700">128</a>
  <a href="#" class="btn m blue border-2 text700 padding-left-5">Plus One
    <i class="fa fa-google-plus fa-lg"></i>
  </a>
</div>
<!-- Example Google End -->

<!-- Example Download Start -->
<div class="btn-addon">
  <a href="#" class="addon m green border border-3 text700">256</a>
  <a href="#" class="btn m green border-3 text700 padding-left-5">
    Download
    <i class="fa fa-download fa-lg"></i>
  </a>
</div>
<!-- Example Download End -->

<!-- Example  Start -->
<div class="btn-addon">
  <a href="#" class="addon m red border border-3 text700 round-left">256</a>
  <a href="#" class="btn m red border-3 text700 round-right padding-left-5">
    Download
    <i class="fa fa-download fa-lg"></i>
  </a>
</div>
<!-- Example Download End -->
```

##### Button Addons Sizes

